CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 10, 1962, pg. 1. Portions of article read: "'Miss Universe' Title Sought By Pittsburgh Area Beauties - Pittsburgh area beauties now are signing up for the Miss Universe Contest for selection of Miss Pittsburgh.  Among the first entries were Velma Reed, 7625 Kelly St.; Alberta Thompson, 2332 LaPlace St., and Dolly Blairman, 3548 Webster Ave. Extension, all of the Marlene Moore Modeling Agency..."Cutline of related images published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 14A, reads: "Holiday House Glistens With D.I.'s Style Show and Dance"
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Alberta Thompson modeling graphic patterned bathing suit and cover up, standing in front of light colored curtain in Holiday House for D. I. Club's "Melody in Fashion" benefit for MENDS
